# ============================================================
# Accepted Risk Register — OWASP Juice Shop DevSecOps Demo
# ============================================================
# Format: CVE-ID
# Each entry MUST have a justification comment above it.
# Reviewed: 2025-01 | Next review: 2025-07
# Owner: @your-github-username
# ============================================================

# [ACCEPTED] HTTP/2 Rapid Reset Attack (CVE-2023-44487)
# Severity: CRITICAL | Component: Node.js runtime (base image)
# Justification: Juice Shop in this demo environment is NOT exposed
# to the public internet. NGINX proxy does not forward HTTP/2 upstream.
# Risk: LOW in current architecture.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-44487
CVE-2023-44487

# [ACCEPTED] runc container escape via /proc/self/exe (CVE-2024-21626)
# Severity: CRITICAL | Component: runc (container runtime)
# Justification: Docker Compose config uses no privileged mode,
# no host PID namespace, no writable host volume mounts.
# Attack requires local access to container host — not applicable in CI/CD.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-21626
CVE-2024-21626

# [ACCEPTED] OpenSSL timing oracle in RSA decryption (CVE-2022-4304)
# Severity: HIGH | Component: openssl (Debian base layer)
# Justification: No TLS termination occurs at the application layer.
# TLS is handled upstream by NGINX which uses a patched openssl version.
# Residual risk from base image layer only.
# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-4304
CVE-2022-4304

# [ACCEPTED] Hardcoded RSA Private Key in insecurity.js
# Severity: HIGH | Component: Juice Shop application (intentional)
# Justification: This is a DELIBERATE vulnerability placed by OWASP
# Juice Shop authors for educational purposes. Not a real credential.
# Documented as pipeline finding in Security Executive Summary.
# Reference: https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop (design decision)
# Note: This suppresses the secret finding in non-enforcement scans only.
# The Quality Gate step still uses --exit-code 1 for CRITICAL vulns.
OWASP-Juice-Shop-Hardcoded-Key

